<text id="A3060T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Pinkey writes back to Kersh asking him to hold on to his chairs until the entire set is done, as he has been sick.</p> 
</div1> 
 
</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">
<head>
<name type="recipient">Mr A. W. Kersh</name>
<name type="place">Port Republic</name>
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1868-11-04"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 4<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1868</date>
</dateline>
<salute>Dear Sir</salute>
</opener>

<p>yours of the 24<hi rend="super">th</hi> to hand I have not been able to get up after those chairs on account of sickness &amp; I <orig reg="can't">cant</orig> <unclear>say</unclear> when I will.  It may be that I will wait <orig reg="until">untill</orig> they are all done, make <del hand="h1">one</del> <unclear>2</unclear> Rocking Chairs with the 5 Sets.</p>

<p>Hold on to them I will be certain to take them. if I dont get up <orig reg="until">untill</orig> you have them all <orig reg="done">don</orig> write to me make the Rocking Chairs high in the back.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Yours <abbr expan="Respectfully">Resp</abbr></salute> 
<signed>A. H. Pinkey</signed> 
<seg type="postscript">Address Port Republic<lb/>Rockingham <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></seg> 

</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
